schleifenbauer.description: This MIB describes the functions of the Schleifenbauer device family.

DeciAmps.name: DeciAmps
DeciAmps.description: Data type for reporting measurements and thresholds associated with current sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 1.1 amp, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 11 DeciAmps. The value is scaled in this manner as a way to deal with floating point types that SNMP does not currently support.

DeciCelsius.name: DeciCelsius
DeciCelsius.description: Data type for reporting sensor readings associated with temperature sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 20.1 degree Celsius, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 201 tenth degrees Celsius. The value is scaled in this manner as a way to deal with floating point types that SNMP does not currently support.

DeciPowerFactor.name: DeciPowerFactor
DeciPowerFactor.description: Data type for reporting measurements associated with power factor calculation. The power factor of an AC power system is defined as the ratio of the real or active power to the apparent power and is a number between 0 and 1. A DeciPowerFactor value is calculated by taking this ratio and multiplying by 1000. A power factor of 98.3% will be reported as 983. The power factor is used to indicate how efficiently a particular load is utilizing energy.

DeciValue.name: DeciValue
DeciValue.description: Data type for reporting generic measurements associated with environmental sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 21.1 degree, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 211 DeciValue. The value is scaled in this manner as a way to deal with floating point types that SNMP does not currently support.

DeciVolts.name: DeciVolts
DeciVolts.description: Data type for reporting measurements and thresholds associated with voltage sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 231.1 volts, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 2311 DeciVolts. The value is scaled in this manner as a way to deal with floating point types that SNMP does not currently support.

KiloWattHour.name: KiloWattHour
KiloWattHour.description: Data type for reporting measurements associated with energy accumulation sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 1 kWh, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 1 kWh. No scaling is performed for this type.

MilliSeconds.name: MilliSeconds
MilliSeconds.description: The unit of duration for some settings

Seconds.name: Seconds
Seconds.description: The unit of duration for some settings

buildNumber.name: buildNumber
buildNumber.description: Date and time of latest build of the firmware.

hardwareAddress.name: hardwareAddress
hardwareAddress.description: Hardware serial number; cannot be changed. Can be used as backup unit address. format as 3 unsigned ints separated by dashes: int - int - int

macAddress.name: macAddress
macAddress.description: The ethernet interfaces unique hardware address.

unitAddress.name: unitAddress
unitAddress.description: User defined address; this will be used for addressing the unit.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: User configurable device name or identifier.

vanityTag.name: vanityTag
vanityTag.description: Characters to be displayed as vanity tekst in display.

noPhases.name: noPhases
noPhases.description: Either zero, one or three for no input metering, single or three phase system

noOutletsTotal.name: noOutletsTotal
noOutletsTotal.description: Total number of outlets, even hardwired without switch/measure modules.

noSwitchedOutlets.name: noSwitchedOutlets
noSwitchedOutlets.description: Number of switched outlets. If outlet numbering is non-contiguous: the highest outlet number.

noMeasuredOutlets.name: noMeasuredOutlets
noMeasuredOutlets.description: Number of measured outlets. If outlet numbering is non-contiguous: the highest outlet number.

noSensors.name: noSensors
noSensors.description: The number of external, digital environmental sensors: 0 for none, 1 to 16 depending on number of reported sensors

maximumLoad.name: maximumLoad
maximumLoad.description: Maximum rated load of device per phase, usually either 16 or 32 A.

deviceStatusCode.name: deviceStatusCode
deviceStatusCode.description: Returns an internal status or error code. 0 = OK, 16 = watchdog timer caused reset, 128 = slave module was reset, 144 = both previous.

temperatureAlert.name: temperatureAlert
temperatureAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to temperature exceeding treshhold; 0= no alert; 1= internal unit temp, 2= external sensor.

inputCurrentAlert.name: inputCurrentAlert
inputCurrentAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to current exceeding treshhold; 0=no alert; 1-3 for input phase.

outputCurrentAlert.name: outputCurrentAlert
outputCurrentAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to current exceeding treshhold; 0=no alert; 1-48 for outlet.

inputVoltageAlert.name: inputVoltageAlert
inputVoltageAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to a voltage dip; 0=no alert; 1-3 for input phase.

oCurrentDropAlert.name: oCurrentDropAlert
oCurrentDropAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to the current of a measured outlet suddenly dropping to near zero, possibly indicating a blown fuse; 0=no alert; 1-48 for outlet.

iCurrentDropAlert.name: iCurrentDropAlert
iCurrentDropAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to the current of a measured input suddenly dropping to near zero, possibly indicating a blown fuse; 0=no alert; 1-3 for phase.

rebootDevice.name: rebootDevice
rebootDevice.description: Warm reboot/reset of device; note: this will have no effect on outlet status!

zeroInputKWhSubtotal.name: zeroInputKWhSubtotal
zeroInputKWhSubtotal.description: Reset of input kWh subtotal counters to zero.

zeroOutKWhSubtotal.name: zeroOutKWhSubtotal
zeroOutKWhSubtotal.description: Reset of outlet kWh subtotal counter to zero.

resetPeakValues.name: resetPeakValues
resetPeakValues.description: Reset all peak values to zero, as well input as output metering, voltages dips, current peaks and temperatures.

peakDuration.name: peakDuration
peakDuration.description: A current peak should last at least [stpkdr] MilliSeconds before an alert is raised; max about a minute.

fixedOutletDelay.name: fixedOutletDelay
fixedOutletDelay.description: Minimal delay between two successive relay switches in milliseconds. Minimal delay is 100 ms. Will always be respected!

powerSaverMode.name: powerSaverMode
powerSaverMode.description: Set backlight on time in seconds; 0 keeps display always on. Note that keeping the backlight on may decrease luminosity over time. Setting this to other values than 10, 60, 120 or 240 is incompatible with the gateway!

outletPowerupMode.name: outletPowerupMode
outletPowerupMode.description: Behaviour of outlet on power-up: 0=off; 1=same state as at power down; 2=same state, but delayed by individual delay timer.

maximumTemperature.name: maximumTemperature
maximumTemperature.description: An alert should be generated whenever the temperature of the first connected T sensor is above this value. Zero means disabled.

displayOrientation.name: displayOrientation
displayOrientation.description: 0 no display; display off; 1 vertical, display on top; 2 vertical, upside down; 3 horizontal, display at left; 4 horizontal, display at right

localAlertReset.name: localAlertReset
localAlertReset.description: Allow alerts to be reset locally on device by pushing one of the buttons. [replaces dipDuration]

currentDropDetection.name: currentDropDetection
currentDropDetection.description: Enables the current drop detection function. 0 = always off (default), 1 = input (s) only, 2 = output(s) only, 3 = both inputs and outputs.

wirelessDisplayPower.name: wirelessDisplayPower
wirelessDisplayPower.description: Controls the transit power of the wireless display transciever (if installed). Set to zero to completely disable the module.

inputmeasuresTable.name: inputmeasuresTable
inputmeasuresTable.description: This table contains all measures related to the measured inputs of the DEVICE. Note: either 1 or 3 channels, depending on number of phases measured.

inputmeasuresEntry.name: inputmeasuresEntry
inputmeasuresEntry.description: The record containing the registers for the channel selected by channelIndex.

channelIndex6.name: channelIndex6
channelIndex6.description: The channel. Its value ranges between 1 and 48, depending on the number of channels, usually 1.

kWhTotalI.name: kWhTotalI
kWhTotalI.description: Either the only phase in a single phase measurement; or one of the three phases in a multiphase measurement.

kWhSubtotalI.name: kWhSubtotalI
kWhSubtotalI.description: kWh subtotal register of the only phase in a single phase measurement; or one of three phases in a multiphase measurement. Reset to zero with [rsimks].

powerFactorI.name: powerFactorI
powerFactorI.description: The effective power factor in percent.

peakCurrentI.name: peakCurrentI
peakCurrentI.description: Peak apparent, RMS current; highest value since last reset of the alerts.

minVoltageI.name: minVoltageI
minVoltageI.description: RMS voltage dip; lowest value since reset of alerts.

powerVAI.name: powerVAI
powerVAI.description: Power value calculated, not in data model of device.

powerWattI.name: powerWattI
powerWattI.description: Power value calculated by the gateway, not in data model of device.

maxInletAmps.name: maxInletAmps
maxInletAmps.description: Maximum current per input phase in A; should last at least [stpkdr] MilliSeconds before triggering an alert.

inputCTratio.name: inputCTratio
inputCTratio.description: The multiplier to use in case of use of /5 current transformers. Defaults to 1.

inputName.name: inputName
inputName.description: User configurable naming of inputs or phases. Useful if channels are used to measure branches..

outletsTable.name: outletsTable
outletsTable.description: This table contains the customer specific settings, determining toutlestablehe behaviour of the DEVICE.

outletsEntry.name: outletsEntry
outletsEntry.description: The record containing the registers forthe channel selected by channelIndex.

channelIndex4.name: channelIndex4
channelIndex4.description: The channel. Its value ranges between 1 and 48, depending on the number of channels, usually 1.

outletName.name: outletName
outletName.description: User configurable naming of individual outlets. Useful to distinguish outlets based on customer or device name.

outputmeasuresTable.name: outputmeasuresTable
outputmeasuresTable.description: This table contains all measures related to the measured outputs of the DEVICE. Note: up to 48 channels, depending on number of measured outlets.

outputmeasuresEntry.name: outputmeasuresEntry
outputmeasuresEntry.description: The record containing the registers for the channel selected by channelIndex.

channelIndex7.name: channelIndex7
channelIndex7.description: The channel. Its value ranges between 1 and 48, depending on the number of channels, usually 1.

kWhSubtotalO.name: kWhSubtotalO
kWhSubtotalO.description: kWh subtotal register of selected output. Reset to zero with [rsomks].

peakCurrentO.name: peakCurrentO
peakCurrentO.description: Peak apparent, RMS current; highest value since last reset of alerts.

maxOutletAmps.name: maxOutletAmps
maxOutletAmps.description: Maximum current per outlet in A; should last at least [stpkdr] MilliSeconds before triggering an alert.

outputCTratio.name: outputCTratio
outputCTratio.description: The multiplier to use in case of use of /5 current transformers. Defaults to 1.

switchedoutletsTable.name: switchedoutletsTable
switchedoutletsTable.description: This table contains the current status of switchable DEVICE's.

switchedoutletsEntry.name: switchedoutletsEntry
switchedoutletsEntry.description: The record containing the registers for the channel selected by channelIndex.

channelIndex5.name: channelIndex5
channelIndex5.description: The channel. Its value ranges between 1 and 48, depending on the number of channels, usually 1.

currentState.name: currentState
currentState.description: The actual state of the outlet relays. The hardware will contain max 48 outlets. Writing is only effective after setting [swounl].

scheduled.name: scheduled
scheduled.description: A one indicates pending activity; the switch delay has not yet expired.

unlock.name: unlock
unlock.description: Setting the value to one will release the safety for this outlet for a couple seconds; switching and rebooting are then temporarily enabled.

individualOutletDelay.name: individualOutletDelay
individualOutletDelay.description: Delay before an individual outlet switches on at power-up in Seconds.

sensorTable.name: sensorTable
sensorTable.description: This table contains the environmental measurements. As well internal temperature as external temperature probes.

sensorEntry.name: sensorEntry
sensorEntry.description: The record containing the registers for the channel selected by channelIndex.

channelIndex8.name: channelIndex8
channelIndex8.description: The channel. Its value ranges between 1 and 48, depending on the number of channels, usually 1.

sensorType.name: sensorType
sensorType.description: Type of connected sensor, either T, H or I for respectively Temperature (C), Humidity (%) or dry switch contact

compliance.name: compliance
compliance.description: The requirements for conformance to the SPGW-MIB.

identificationGroup.name: identificationGroup
identificationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing identification information about the device.

configurationGroup.name: configurationGroup
configurationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information about the device.

systemStatusGroup.name: systemStatusGroup
systemStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status information about the device.

resetGroup.name: resetGroup
resetGroup.description: Groups resettable attributes op the device.

settingsGroup.name: settingsGroup
settingsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual settings about the device.

switchedOutletsGroup.name: switchedOutletsGroup
switchedOutletsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual outlet status of the device.

inputMeasuresGroup.name: inputMeasuresGroup
inputMeasuresGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual input measurements of the device.

outputMeasuresGroup.name: outputMeasuresGroup
outputMeasuresGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual output measurements of the device.

sensorsGroup.name: sensorsGroup
sensorsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual environmental measurements of the device.
